<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Understanding suspense items</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  In council finance, a "suspense item" is a payment that has been received but cannot be automatically allocated to an account. This happens when:
</p>

<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li>A payment arrives with an incorrect or missing reference number</li>
  <li>A bank transfer doesn't match any known account</li>
  <li>A payment amount doesn't match any outstanding balance</li>
  <li>A resident pays into the wrong fund</li>
</ul>

<p class="govuk-body">
  Finance officers must review these items and manually allocate them to the correct accounts. This is one of the most time-consuming tasks in council income management.
</p>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Review the suspense queue</h3>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>
    <strong>Navigate to suspense management</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      From the admin portal, navigate to the suspense management section. You'll see a list of payments that need manual allocation.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Review a suspense item</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Click on a suspense item to see its details:
    </p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li><strong>Payment amount</strong> — how much was received</li>
      <li><strong>Payment source</strong> — where the payment came from (bank transfer, card, etc.)</li>
      <li><strong>Date received</strong> — when the payment arrived</li>
      <li><strong>Reference provided</strong> — any reference the payer included</li>
      <li><strong>Reason for suspense</strong> — why it couldn't be auto-allocated</li>
    </ul>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Search for the matching account</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Use the reference or amount to search for potential matching accounts. The system may suggest likely matches based on the payment details.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Allocate the payment</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Once you've identified the correct account, allocate the payment. Select the account, confirm the allocation, and the payment will be moved from suspense to the account's transaction history.
    </p>
  </li>
</ol>

<div class="govuk-inset-text">
  <strong>Why this matters:</strong> Unresolved suspense items represent money that hasn't been properly accounted for. Councils are required to keep suspense balances as low as possible for audit compliance. An efficient suspense management workflow directly impacts the accuracy of financial reporting and reduces the risk of audit findings.
</div>

